The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for solving combinatorial optimization problems on graphs, which involves using Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN) and Q-learning. This work involves machine learning techniques and optimization problems, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with social network analysis and influence maximization, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
